<item>
            <title>[LU-13755] no effect assignment in sptlrpc_lproc_init()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13755</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Seems to be added by 218fc688c11f081881b2cc1c1632ceaf9ec77a77 &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12401&quot; title=&quot;Various issues with checksum calculation for Kerberos and SSK&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12401&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12401&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; gss: fix checksum for Kerberos and SSK&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;+       sptlrpc_lprocfs_dir = lprocfs_register(&quot;sptlrpc&quot;, proc_lustre_root,
+                                              NULL, NULL);
+       if (IS_ERR_OR_NULL(sptlrpc_lprocfs_dir)) {
+               rc = PTR_ERR(sptlrpc_lprocfs_dir);
+               rc = sptlrpc_lprocfs_dir ? PTR_ERR(sptlrpc_lprocfs_dir)
+                       : -ENOMEM;
+               sptlrpc_lprocfs_dir = NULL;
+       }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;that first &apos;rc =&apos; line does not make any sense, does it?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
